From d2add990c98a01c8e679a77f816d346d6c5064d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 19:30:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: widen Now Playing freshness window based on real
 evidence

Root-caused via live heartbeat tracing during an active watch
session: isActivelyWatching()'s 7.5min window (v1.9.26) was still
too tight for Nuvio's actual checkpoint cadence. Direct evidence: a
genuinely continuous playback session had a real 13.4-minute gap
between two Nuvio checkpoints, so even the widened v1.9.26 window
produced a false negative. hasRecentActivity (a separate check in
the same file, using a 15min/3x window) correctly evaluated the
exact same data as recent - but wasn't the check actually gating
session creation, so the discrepancy between the two never surfaced
until traced directly.

Widened isActivelyWatching to 20min/4x, matching and slightly
exceeding hasRecentActivity's window. Removed the item-specific
hardcoded tracing (tt37287335) added for this investigation; kept
the general heartbeat() infrastructure, which proved broadly useful
for this and future debugging.

Bump to 1.9.32, changelog entry added.
